quagga.input.subject: FW: FW: Fw: READ THIS BEFORE YOU LOOK AT THE PIC
quagga.input.body:
---------------------- Forwarded by Sara Shackleton/HOU/ECT on 03/24/2000 
05:40 PM ---------------------------


"CAVALIER,D. MD" <LAB-DSC@womans.com> on 03/23/2000 02:44:04 PM
To: "'Sara Shackleton'" <sshackl@ect.enron.com>
cc:  (bcc: Sara Shackleton/HOU/ECT)
Subject: FW: FW: Fw: READ THIS BEFORE YOU LOOK AT THE PIC





> -----Original Message-----
> From: PARRISH,LORI B
> Sent: Thursday, March 23, 2000 8:39 AM
> To: CAVALIER,D. MD
> Subject: FW: FW: Fw: READ THIS BEFORE YOU LOOK AT THE PIC
>
> FOR YOU
>
> -----Original Message-----
> From: HORNE,BECKY B
> Sent: Thursday, March 23, 2000 8:36 AM
> To: PARRISH,LORI B
> Subject: FW: FW: Fw: READ THIS BEFORE YOU LOOK AT THE PIC
>
>
>
> -----Original Message-----
> From: LABORDE,JEANNE M
> Sent: Thursday, March 23, 2000 7:50 AM
> To: HORNE,BECKY B
> Subject: FW: FW: Fw: READ THIS BEFORE YOU LOOK AT THE PIC
>
>
>
> -----Original Message-----
> From: sorihuela@wm.com [SMTP:sorihuela@wm.com]
> Sent: Wednesday, March 22, 2000 3:11 PM
> To: LAB-JML@womans.com
> Subject: Re: FW: Fw: READ THIS BEFORE YOU LOOK AT THE PIC
>
> >
> >
> > READ THIS BEFORE YOU LOOK AT THE PHOTO
> >
> > How much does this guy like biking?!  This ad appeared in the Arkansas
> > Democrat-Gazette on Thursday June 17th.  The unfortunate photographic
> > illusion was quickly noticed (look at the bike seat) and action was
> taken
> > to correct the advertisement, but not before the image made it to the
> > newsstand.  They should have used a bike seat that was not tan in color.
> >
> >
> >
> >
> >  <<BIKER.jpg>> (See attached file: BIKER.jpg)
>
>
>
>
>
>
>
>
>
>  <<JPEG File Interchange>>

 - BIKER.jpg
